---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Norway Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/norway/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Sweden for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/sweden' },
  { title: 'Denmark for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/denmark' },
  { title: 'Finland for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/finland' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'norwayFit', header: 'Norway Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'NOK 4,500-6,200/mo', norwayFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'NOK 5,200-7,200/mo', norwayFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'NOK 4,100-5,700/mo', norwayFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'AXA Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'NOK 3,800-5,400/mo', norwayFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Norwegian Public (Helfo)', entryAge: 'No limit', renewal: 'N/A', monthlyFrom: 'Tax-funded', norwayFit: 'For Residents' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'NOK 4,100-6,200', annual: 'NOK 49,200-74,400' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'NOK 5,600-8,000', annual: 'NOK 67,200-96,000' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'NOK 7,500-10,800', annual: 'NOK 90,000-129,600' },
  { category: 'Norwegian Public Healthcare', monthly: 'Tax-funded', annual: 'Max NOK 3,165 co-pays' },
  { category: 'Norwegian Private Treatment', monthly: 'NOK 500-1,500', annual: 'NOK 6,000-18,000' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Norway 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Norway. Public healthcare, Oslo hospitals, fjord living, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Norway"
  subheadline="Norway offers spectacular nature, excellent healthcare, and high living standards—funded by oil wealth but with restrictive immigration for non-EU retirees."
  heroImage="/images/countries/norway-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Norway</h2>
  <p>
    Norway offers stunning natural beauty, from fjords to Northern Lights, combined with one of the world's highest living standards. Oil wealth funds excellent public services including healthcare. The country consistently ranks among the best for quality of life and happiness.
  </p>

  <p>
    Oslo provides urban amenities with fjord access. Bergen offers dramatic western coast scenery. Trondheim and Tromsø appeal to those seeking northern adventures. Smaller coastal towns combine natural beauty with adequate healthcare access.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Excellent; tax-funded with small co-pays</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Norwegian; English widely spoken</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> NOK 25,000-45,000/month (~€2,200-4,000); very high</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Varies; milder coast, cold interior/north</li>
      <li><strong>EU Status:</strong> Not EU but EEA member; Schengen zone</li>
      <li><strong>Nature:</strong> Spectacular fjords, mountains, Northern Lights</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Norway's Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Norway's healthcare is primarily public, funded through taxes and managed by regional health authorities. Residents pay small co-payments (egenandel) capped at NOK 3,165/year (frikort exemption card). After reaching the cap, further treatment is free.
  </p>

  <p>
    Quality is excellent with modern hospitals and well-trained staff. GPs (fastlege) are your first point of contact. Wait times for specialists vary; urgent cases are prioritized. Some Norwegians add private insurance for faster elective care access.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Fastlege (GP) Assignment</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      All residents are assigned a GP (fastlege). You can request a specific doctor, but popular GPs may have waiting lists. Your fastlege handles routine care and referrals to specialists. Building a relationship with your GP is important in the Norwegian system.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Norway's immigration is restrictive for non-EEA retirees:
  </p>

  <h3>Family Immigration</h3>
  <p>
    If you have a Norwegian citizen or resident spouse/partner, family reunification is possible. The Norwegian family member must meet income requirements (currently ~NOK 300,000/year).
  </p>

  <h3>Self-Employment</h3>
  <p>
    Starting a business in Norway requires significant investment and job creation. Not practical for most retirees but possible for those with business interests.
  </p>

  <h3>EEA/EFTA Citizens</h3>
  <p>
    EEA citizens (EU plus Iceland, Liechtenstein) and Swiss citizens have freedom of movement. Register with police after 3 months. Demonstrate sufficient resources and health coverage.
  </p>

  <h3>No Retirement Visa</h3>
  <p>
    Norway doesn't have a retirement visa. Non-EEA nationals need qualifying circumstances like family, work, or study.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Norway:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Residence application:</strong> Comprehensive health insurance required</li>
    <li><strong>EEA citizens:</strong> EHIC initially; register with Helfo for Norwegian coverage</li>
    <li><strong>After registration:</strong> Full access to Norwegian healthcare with co-pays</li>
    <li><strong>Private option:</strong> Some add for faster specialist access</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Norway</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance is essential for residence applications. Once registered with Helfo, Norwegian healthcare covers most needs affordably (max NOK 3,165/year co-pays). Some add private treatment insurance for faster elective care. Keep international coverage for travel and home country visits.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Norway, these providers offer appropriate coverage:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Norway</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Strong Scandinavian network, good for initial period</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz Care:</strong> Competitive European pricing</li>
    <li><strong>Norwegian Private:</strong> Vertikal Helse, IF offer treatment insurance</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage and pricing from providers that accept seniors for Norway.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Norway are high, reflecting local prices:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Get registered:</strong> Norwegian public healthcare is excellent and affordable</li>
    <li><strong>Frikort:</strong> After NOK 3,165 in co-pays, you get exemption card for rest of year</li>
    <li><strong>Norway exclusion:</strong> Once registered, exclude Norway from international policy</li>
    <li><strong>Private Norwegian:</strong> Cheaper than international for faster local care</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: American with Norwegian Spouse, 67</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Married to Norwegian citizen. Moving to Bergen via family reunification.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global for application. After Helfo registration, Norwegian system. Keep Cigna for US visits.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Initially ~NOK 5,500/month. After: max NOK 264/month co-pays + Cigna ~NOK 3,500/month (Norway excluded).</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: Swedish EU Citizen, 72</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> EEA citizen moving from Stockholm to Oslo. Swedish pension.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> EEA rights apply. Register with Helfo for Norwegian healthcare. Add private for faster specialist access.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Public with co-pay cap + Norwegian private ~NOK 800/month. BUPA for Sweden visits.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: British Post-Brexit, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> UK citizen, no longer EEA. Has Norwegian partner of 10 years.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Family reunification via cohabitation. BUPA Global for application. Norwegian system after approval.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Initially ~NOK 6,500/month. After registration: co-pays + BUPA ~NOK 4,000/month (Norway excluded).</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I retire to Norway without Norwegian family?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Very difficult for non-EEA nationals. Norway doesn't have a retirement visa or financial independence pathway. You typically need: Norwegian spouse/partner, work permit, or business. EEA citizens (EU plus Iceland, Liechtenstein, Switzerland) have freedom of movement.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How expensive is Norway really?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Very expensive—among the world's highest costs. Oslo is particularly pricey. However, healthcare costs are capped (NOK 3,165/year), salaries/pensions are high, and quality of life is excellent. Budget carefully; restaurant meals and alcohol are notably expensive.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What is the frikort?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Once you've paid NOK 3,165 in approved co-payments (egenandeler) in a calendar year, you receive a frikort (exemption card). This makes further medical care, prescriptions, and some travel costs free for the rest of the year. It's automatic—you don't need to apply.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How dark are Norwegian winters?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Depends on location. Oslo gets ~6 hours of daylight in December. Bergen has more cloud but similar daylight. Tromsø (north) experiences polar night with no sun for weeks. Many Norwegians use light therapy and embrace outdoor activities despite darkness.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers that specialize in senior expat coverage for Norway.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Norwegian immigration (UDI) and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
